%N A395001 Sequence generated by the D'Hondt (or Jefferson) apportionment method applied to the weights p(k) = 1/sqrt(k), k >= 1.
%C A395001 The D'Hondt method is applicable even though the sum of the weights is infinite.
%C A395001 a(n) is the smallest number k minimizing (c(k)+1)/p(k), where c(k) is the number of occurrences of k among the previous terms. Ties occur at n = 4, 9, 11, 15, 20, 21, 24, 27, 32, ... .
%C A395001 A007913 is the subsequence of squarefree terms.
%C A395001 A083855 is the subsequence of terms equal to 1, 2, 3, or 6.
%H A395001 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A395001/b395001.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395001 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%27Hondt_method">D'Hondt method</a>.
%Y A395001 Cf. A007913, A027750 (weights p(k) = 1/k), A083855, A395000.
%K A395001 nonn
%O A395001 1,2
%A A395001 _Pontus von Brömssen_, Apr 10 2026
